---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ResonantDAO Membership - ResonantOS" description="ResonantDAO membership is issued through official non-transferable Manifesto and Community Member NFT credentials.">
	<section class="px-4 pb-16 pt-14 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
			<p class="mb-5 font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-emerald-400">Membership</p>
			<h1 class="text-5xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-6xl">One wallet. One official Community credential.</h1>
			<p class="mt-8 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-8 text-zinc-300">
				The Community Member NFT is the base access credential for ResonantDAO. It proves that a wallet is part of the DAO and can interact with member-gated smart contracts.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Combined Registration</h2>
				<p class="mt-4 text-zinc-400">
					The preferred website flow mints the Augmentatism Manifesto NFT and the Community Member NFT together. The user signs the Manifesto, the program records the proof, and the wallet becomes an active Community Member in one transaction flow.
				</p>
			</div>
			<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">On-Chain One-Per-Wallet Rule</h2>
				<p class="mt-4 text-zinc-400">
					The membership record is derived from the wallet address. If an active record already exists, the program rejects another Community credential for that wallet.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl rounded-lg border border-emerald-400/20 bg-emerald-400/[0.06] p-6">
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Registration Flow</h2>
			<ol class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-zinc-300">
				<li>1. Connect a wallet.</li>
				<li>2. Read and sign the canonical Augmentatism Manifesto.</li>
				<li>3. The Membership Program derives the wallet's member record.</li>
				<li>4. The program mints non-transferable Manifesto and Community credentials.</li>
				<li>5. The credentials are recorded in the official MemberRecord.</li>
				<li>6. DAO contracts can verify the wallet as an active Community Member.</li>
			</ol>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">What Membership Unlocks</h2>
			<div class="mt-8 grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-3">
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">DAO Contract Access</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">Bounty claims, proposals, contribution records, protocol access, and future DAO workflows can require active membership.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contribution Reputation</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">The wallet becomes the long-term home for contribution level, domain reputation, tenure, and activity history.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="rounded-lg border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.03] p-6">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Future Governance</h3>
					<p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">Human governance rights are planned around verified membership and earned reputation, not transferable capital alone.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
